[1]
Date: 16 Jun 2011
Source: Taiwan News/AP [edited[
http://www.taiwannews.com.tw/etn/news_content.php?id=1627671


Anthrax found in 2 Serbian villages
-----------------------------------
Serbian authorities have declared 2 northern villages an
anthrax-infected zone after the bacteria [sic] was found in animals
there. The Agriculture ministry says it has launched vaccination of
cattle in the villages of Bocar and Novo Milosevo. The ministry says
it has banned the use of milk and meat from the animals in those
villages.

The statement on Thursday [16 Jun 2011] says that "the situation in
the field is stable with minimum possibility for the spread of the
disease." Anthrax bacteria spores lie dormant in the soil and can
become active under conditions such as heavy rainfall, flooding or
drought. Animals that aren't vaccinated often die quickly after being
exposed to the bacteria.

--
