[Anthrax historically has been erratically reported in Serbia, and
the country only became independent recently. It has probably been
occurring in the background for some time. If it is as infrequent as
they claim it would be wiser to annually vaccinate herds in target
areas; i.e., for these outbreaks and Tutin, for 5 years and then watch
carefully to see if it recurs.

Surveillance of unexpected deaths is a key part of anthrax control.
When outbreaks occur in areas which have truly not seen the disease in
decades it is usually the result of earth moving activities -- ditch
and spring clearing, putting in water lines to new cattle
water-troughs in old pastures, bulldozing scrub and roads, dredging
rivers and streams downstream of mills and tanneries.

To find Vojvodina, go to:
http://www.fallingrain.com/world/RI/00/Vojvodinci.html - Mod.MHJ]

